 Days in Prague, Director of the ONE Conference Prague 2013 and One Conference Brussels 2014.'),(1793,478,'bio','Director and co-founder of EPMA'),(1794,478,'description',''),(1795,478,'time',''),(1796,478,'speaker',''),(1797,478,'_edit_lock','1389732056:1'),(1798,479,'_wp_attached_file','2014/01/irina3.jpg'),(1799,479,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:5:{s:5:\"width\";i:564;s:6:\"height\";i:846;s:4:\"file\";s:18:\"2014/01/irina3.jpg\";s:5:\"sizes\";a:2:{s:9:\"thumbnail\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:16:\"irina3-50x50.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:50;s:6:\"height\";i:50;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}s:6:\"medium\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:18:\"irina3-200x300.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:200;s:6:\"height\";i:300;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}}s:10:\"image_meta\";a:10:{s:8:\"aperture\";i:0;s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";i:0;s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";i:0;s:3:\"iso\";i:0;s:13:\"shutter_speed\";i:0;s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";}}'),(1800,478,'_edit_last','1'),(1801,480,'_wp_attached_file','2014/01/irina3.png'),(1802,480,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:5:{s:5:\"width\";i:497;s:6:\"height\";i:497;s:4:\"file\";s:18:\"2014/01/irina3.png\";s:5:\"sizes\";a:2:{s:9:\"thumbnail\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:16:\"irina3-50x50.png\";s:5:\"width\";i:50;s:6:\"height\";i:50;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:9:\"image/png\";}s:6:\"medium\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:18:\"irina3-300x300.png\";s:5:\"width\";i:300;s:6:\"height\";i:300;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:9:\"image/png\";}}s:10:\"image_meta\";a:10:{s:8:\"aperture\";i:0;s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";i:0;s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";i:0;s:3:\"iso\";i:0;s:13:\"shutter_speed\";i:0;s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";}}'),(1803,478,'_thumbnail_id','480'),(1804,478,'_wpas_done_all','1'),(1805,481,'biography',''),(1806,481,'bio',''),(1807,481,'description','Regions need to re-estimate their own capacity to plan, assess and manage investments in all fields, especially in the field of ICT. The data economy calls for new thinking on governance, but policymakers face a number of obstacles, falling to predict future development and adequately respond to societal challenges.\r\nThe new approach is suggested by ONE project, www.oneproject.eu, how to combine: Knowledge Base, Public Intelligence, and Common Sense, using experiences of regional ICT observatories. The journey includes gathering of local data, aggregating, creating indicators, using metadata and analytical tools, processing Big data and Open data, visualisation, creating analysis for decision-making and helping to shape local, regional and European policies.\r\n'),(1808,481,'time','10:00-10:30'),(1809,481,'speaker','478;'),(1810,481,'_edit_lock','1389733093:1'),(1811,481,'_edit_last','1'),(1812,481,'_wpas_done_all','1'),(1813,483,'biography',''),(1814,483,'bio',''),(1815,483,'description','<p>Governments around Europe are in the process of releasing huge amounts of data as open data. But the reuse of this data still remains below expectations. The Open Data Support project of DG CONNECT, presented in this session, aims to improve the visibility and facilitate the access to datasets published on local and national open data portals in order to increase their reuse within and across borders. </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>In order to achieve this, Open Data Supports puts in place a central repository that hosts description metadata of datasets from EU Member States and Institutions, harmonised according to the DCAT Application Profile for data portals in Europe. Hence, reusers can browse and access a wealth of datasets using a common vocabulary. </p>\r\n'),(1816,483,'time','10:30-11:00'),(1817,483,'speaker','476;'),(1818,483,'_edit_last','1'),(1819,483,'_edit_lock','1389790734:1'),(1820,483,'_wpas_done_all','1'),(1821,1,'biography',''),(1822,1,'bio',''),(1823,1,'description',''),(1824,1,'time',''),(1825,1,'speaker',''),(1826,206,'_wp_old_slug','geodata'),(1827,486,'biography','Since 4 years actively engaged with policy making in Amsterdam concerning Open Innovation Open Data. Promoting the value of open source, interoperable technological solutions for cities.\r\nShe is coordinating currently 3 EU Innovation projects (Code4EU, Open Cities, City SDK) in Amsterdam to show the added value for Open Data, Open Source App Development and working with commons and smart toolkits of interoperable mobile app interfaces in cities. Responsible launching an OPen Innovation Program in Amsterdam . Engaged with creating new projects, and proposals (HORIZON2020) around Open Data / Big Data, Tech Acceleration and new SME\'s fundings. She operates between city governance, hackers, start ups and innovation agencies and believer of bottom up civic innovation and non proprietary open source operating systems.\r\n'),(1828,486,'bio','Open Innovation Policy Advisor, City of Amsterdam, Economic Development'),(1829,486,'description',''),(1830,486,'time',''),(1831,486,'speaker',''),(1832,486,'_edit_last','1'),(1833,486,'_edit_lock','1389804082:1'),(1834,487,'_wp_attached_file','2014/01/profile-photo.jpg'),(1835,487,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:5:{s:5:\"width\";i:500;s:6:\"height\";i:375;s:4:\"file\";s:25:\"2014/01/profile-photo.jpg\";s:5:\"sizes\";a:2:{s:9:\"thumbnail\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:23:\"profile-photo-50x50.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:50;s:6:\"height\";i:50;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}s:6:\"medium\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:25:\"profile-photo-300x225.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:300;s:6:\"height\";i:225;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}}s:10:\"image_meta\";a:10:{s:8:\"aperture\";i:0;s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";i:0;s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";i:0;s:3:\"iso\";i:0;s:13:\"shutter_speed\";i:0;s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";}}'),(1836,486,'_thumbnail_id','487'),(1837,486,'_wpas_done_all','1'),(1838,488,'_wp_attached_file','2013/12/vassilios-peristeras.jpg'),