ve-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(360,2,'2013-12-20 09:56:39','2013-12-20 09:56:39','','Frank-De-Saer','','inherit','closed','open','','frank-de-saer','','','2013-12-20 09:56:39','2013-12-20 09:56:39','',327,'http://www.datadays.eu/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/Frank-De-Saer.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(361,2,'2013-12-20 10:08:34','2013-12-20 10:08:34','','Mr. Pieter Colpaert','','inherit','closed','open','','340-autosave-v1','','','2013-12-20 10:08:34','2013-12-20 10:08:34','',340,'http://www.datadays.eu/340-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(362,2,'2013-12-20 10:30:56','2013-12-20 10:30:56','','AndrewStott','','inherit','closed','open','','andrewstott','','','2013-12-20 10:30:56','2013-12-20 10:30:56','',342,'http://www.datadays.eu/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/AndrewStott.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(363,1,'2013-12-20 12:07:17','2013-12-20 12:07:17','<h3>Context</h3>\r\nCitadel on the Move is a European project that aims to provide a common European market for mobile applications. More and more European cities are publishing Open Data in an interoperable way, so that applications developed for one city may be reused in another. Citadel provides the tools build such an application quickly.\r\n\r\n<h3>Challenge</h3>\r\nDesign and build a working prototype of an application that works in at least two of the four Citadel Pilot cities, using local open data. (<a href=\"http://www.citadelonthemove.eu/en-us/thehub/opendata.aspx\" title=\"get the data here!\" target=\"_blank\">get the data here!</a>)\r\n\r\n• Issy-les-Moulineaux\r\n• Manchester\r\n• Athens\r\n• Ghent\r\n\r\nYour application can be situated in the domain of mobility, tourism or city life in general.\r\n\r\nTo help you get started, a number of open source application templates are made available here. Using these templates is not required to win the challenge.\r\n\r\n<h3>Reward</h3>\r\nThe winner of this challenge wins a cash prize of cash prize of <b>EUR 5000</b> and is invited to one of the pilot cities in May-August 2014 to test his/her application in real life!\r\nThe flight is paid for by the project, and you arrange your own lodgings and arrival/departure dates.\r\n\r\n<h3>Criteria</h3>\r\nParticipation to this challenge is an individual commitment. Your application will be scored based on the added value for life in the city and the quality of your implementation.\r\nAll submissions are due <b>before February 10th 2014</b>.\r\n\r\n<h3>Jury</h3>\r\nTo apply, you should send your application to your local representative (using the form below). One application is selected in each of the pilot cities to compete for the prize on February 1st, 2014. An international jury will deliberate the 4 selected applications and announce the winner during the Data Days conference in Ghent, the 18th of February.\r\n\r\n<h3>Apply!</h3>\r\nThe form below will be submitted to the representative of your city. \r\n[contact-form-7 id=\"11\" title=\"Apply!\"]','Citadel Hackathon','','publish','closed','open','','hackathon-citadel','','','2014-01-09 09:53:29','2014-01-09 09:53:29','',0,'http://www.datadays.eu/?page_id=363',0,'page','',0),(364,1,'2013-12-20 12:07:17','2013-12-20 12:07:17','[contact-form-7 id=\"11\" title=\"Apply!\"]','','','inherit','closed','open','','363-revision-v1','','','2013-12-20 12:07:17','2013-12-20 12:07:17','',363,'http://www.datadays.eu/363-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(365,1,'2013-12-20 12:07:35','2013-12-20 12:07:35','[contact-form-7 id=\"11\" title=\"Apply!\"]','Citadel Hackathon','','inherit','closed','open','','363-revision-v1','','','2013-12-20 12:07:35','2013-12-20 12:07:35','',363,'http://www.datadays.eu/363-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(366,2,'2013-12-20 12:22:20','2013-12-20 12:22:20','Join the <a title=\"Open Knowledge Foundation Belgium\" href=\"http://okfn.be\" target=\"_blank\">Open Knowledge Foundation Belgium</a> on the 17th February. Open Belgium will host several keynote speeches Open Data by policy makers in Flanders, Wallonia and Belgium. Break-out rooms will also host various workshops on specific subjects such as Open Transport in Belgium, Open Street Map in Belgium, the use of creative commons licenses, and the Belgian datasets that are most wanted to be opened up next.\r\n[sessions day=open-belgium-2]','Day 1: Open Belgium - February, 17th','','inherit','closed','open','','162-revision-v1','','','2013-12-20 12:22:20','2013-12-20 12:22:20','',162,'http://www.datadays.eu/162-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(367,2,'2013-12-20 12:23:53','2013-12-20 12:23:53','<a title=\"Citadel on the Move\" href=\"http://citadelonthemove.eu\" target=\"_blank\">Citadel on the Move</a> presents an Open forum to policy makers and influencers alike to discuss the future of Open Data in Europe. The first results of the project that allows cities to publish their data in a way they can easily be used in a mobile app will be demonstrated. And the winners of the Hackaton come on stage to show their apps.\r\n\r\n[sessions day=open-europe-2]','Day 2: Open Europe - February, 18th','','inherit','closed','open','','165-revision-v1','','','2013-12-20 12:23:53','2013-12-20 12:23:53','',165,'http://www.datadays.eu/165-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(368,2,'2013-12-20 12:24:52','2013-12-20 12:24:52','Open Data is a global phenomenon. Its true implications only become apparent when looking across border, across continents. The Data Days provide a platform for experts and enthusiasts from all over the world to get in touch, share experiences and exchange strategies so that Open Data may shape the future for all of us.  Key topics will include interoperability of Open Data between European cities and regions, Open Data licensing and business models.\r\n\r\n[sessions day=open-world-2]','Day 3: Open World - February 19th','','inherit','closed','open','','167-revision-v1','','','2013-12-20 12:24:52','2013-12-20 12:24:52','',167,'http://www.datadays.eu/167-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(369,2,'2013-12-20 12:36:13','2013-1