negrachts.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(378,1,'2013-12-20 17:20:09','2013-12-20 17:20:09','<h3>Context</h3>\r\nCitadel on the Move is a European project that aims to provide a common European market for mobile applications. More and more European cities are publishing Open Data in an interoperable way, so that applications developed for one city may be reused in another. Citadel provides the tools build such an application quickly.\r\n\r\n<h3>Challenge</h3>\r\nDesign and build a working prototype of an application that works in at least two of the four Citadel Pilot cities, using local open data. (<a href=\"http://www.citadelonthemove.eu/en-us/thehub/opendata.aspx\" title=\"get the data here!\" target=\"_blank\">get the data here!</a>)\r\n\r\n• Issy-les-Moulineaux\r\n• Manchester\r\n• Athens\r\n• Ghent\r\n\r\nYour application can be situated in the domain of mobility, tourism or city life in general.\r\n\r\nTo help you get started, a number of open source application templates are made available here. Using these templates is not required to win the challenge.\r\n\r\n<h3>Reward</h3>\r\nThe winner of this challenge wins a cash prize of cash prize of <b>EUR 5000</b> and is invited to one of the pilot cities in May-August 2014 to test his/her application in real life!\r\nThe flight is paid for by the project, and you arrange your own lodgings and arrival/departure dates.\r\n\r\n<h3>Criteria</h3>\r\nTo be eligible for this challenge, you should be a citizen of either of the pilot cities. Your application will be scored based on the added value for life in the city and the quality of your implementation.\r\n\r\n<h3>Jury</h3>\r\nTo apply, you should send your application to your local representative (using the form below). One application is selected in each of the pilot cities to compete for the prize on February 1st, 2014. An international jury will deliberate the 4 selected applications and announce the winner during the Data Days conference in Ghent, the 18th o